{
  "stem": "23428.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I think it must have been 1936 or possibly 1937, when-- suddenly when my mother asked us one day into her salon in the same place, in Bendlerstrasse-- my father was gone already-- and told us that we were legal Jews, which obviously at that time, even for a nine-year-old, meant that we were second-class citizens.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and in fact, our ethnic identity as Germans was denied to us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was-- both of us children were baptized within a week of our birth as Roman Catholics, since both of my parents were practicing and actually rather religious Roman Catholics.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father, I think, since I suspect he was baptized with his brother-- together with his brother Fritz in Budapest when he was 12 or 13.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was a young teenager.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my mother was baptized in 1932 after I was born, five years after I was born.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But she is certainly the one who is the most religious.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "To the present day, I mean, she is a daily church-goer, to the present day, while I have abandoned religion entirely since I'm in my early 20s.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't think so--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't think so.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In fact, I think religion in prison and in concentration camp probably helped me a good deal to survive.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, I remember kneeling and praying with my brother in prison every night.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And-- and I remember at the very first-- the first weekend after liberation by the Red Army in Auschwitz, I walked something like 10 kilometers to the next church to attend mass.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I was quite religious.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At the time it has helped me.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
